reviewText:
This is a great dvd of the International Harvester equipment advertising films from the 1940s.  I loved seeing all the "new" advertising for the Farmall Cub that comes in this video.
Out of the three Farmall Classic Films DVDs this one is my least favorite because half of it is about Soil Conservation rather than the IH advertising.  Not much tractor action in that segment.
But overall I still really enjoyed the DVD.
This came sooner than I thought it would  very nice book.

These are very interesting videos - not just about tractors, but about the soil conservation efforts being made at this time. I have enjoyed watching it several times with my children. There was a good deal about the Farmall Cub Tractor in this video collection.
I bought this for a Christmas present to my dad. He loves it. And it got here super fast. I ordered it on a Friday got it on a Monday fast. Thank you!
Was disappointed in this cd I thought it would be more on the tractor history and how they are built instead of how farming was done and agriculture.
